WEBVTT

00:01.151 --> 00:02.242
<i> Previously</i>
<i> on "Our Kind of People"...</i>

00:02.244 --> 00:05.153
I think Teddy supplied crack
to Edgartown

00:05.155 --> 00:05.820
and let my mother
take the fall for it.

00:06.340 --> 00:08.565
Teddy keeps journals
in his home office.

00:08.567 --> 00:10.175
Angela, he can't know
that we're together.

00:10.177 --> 00:12.494
I just want this cotillion
to be perfect.

00:12.496 --> 00:14.588
Nikki: I'm being
introduced into society.

00:14.590 --> 00:18.425
I just have to find
a father figure to dance with.

00:18.427 --> 00:21.353
Nate: Nikki needs a father.
After 17 years.

00:21.355 --> 00:22.596
Lauren: Starting over
is a big deal,

00:22.598 --> 00:25.006
especially for someone
who has a criminal record.

00:25.008 --> 00:26.099
Why, Lauren?

00:26.101 --> 00:28.343
I watched you
kiss my girlfriend.

00:28.345 --> 00:30.029
I don't want to be around
you anymore.

00:30.031 --> 00:31.196
You're out of cotillion.

00:31.198 --> 00:32.698
I'm gonna destroy
Teddy Franklin.

00:32.700 --> 00:33.940
What's the plan?

00:33.942 --> 00:35.034
Raymond:
Alex Rivera.

00:35.036 --> 00:36.351
I would think twice

00:36.353 --> 00:37.870
before bringing her
back into our lives.

00:37.872 --> 00:39.371
Teddy: The strength of
the tremors have picked up.

00:39.373 --> 00:42.023
Leah: How long are you going
to keep it a secret?

00:42.025 --> 00:43.267
Tyrique:
We better get back.

00:43.269 --> 00:45.502
We don't want them
wondering where we are.

00:47.289 --> 00:50.440
Dr. Keller, it was no more
than a dizzy spell.

00:50.442 --> 00:52.626
Dr. Keller:<i> Which could have</i>
<i> been much worse.</i>

00:52.628 --> 00:55.128
<i> If you keep ignoring</i>
<i> my medical advice,</i>

00:55.130 --> 00:56.963
<i> I'll have to</i>
<i> discontinue --</i>

00:56.965 --> 00:59.116
Do that,
and my endowment

00:59.118 --> 01:01.876
to your institute in Geneva
will discontinue.

01:01.878 --> 01:04.121
Understood?

01:04.123 --> 01:05.305
Good morning.

01:05.307 --> 01:06.732
[ Sighs ]
Good morning.

01:06.734 --> 01:09.026
Please,
sit down.

01:11.630 --> 01:13.721
I, uh...

01:13.723 --> 01:15.465
I called you here
this morning

01:15.467 --> 01:18.893
because when
I excused myself

01:18.895 --> 01:22.897
from dinner
the other evening...

01:22.899 --> 01:27.160
I saw you
and Angela...

01:27.162 --> 01:30.497
slip out
of my office.

01:30.499 --> 01:33.092
♪♪

01:33.094 --> 01:35.652
Is that why
the cameras have gone dark

01:35.654 --> 01:36.911
at Eve's Crown?

01:36.913 --> 01:40.824
Are you involved
with her?

01:40.826 --> 01:42.008
I'm sorry,
Teddy.

01:42.010 --> 01:43.994
I-I couldn't
keep spying on her.

01:43.996 --> 01:46.921
Mm-hmm.

01:46.923 --> 01:50.091
This is a knot
of my own design.

01:50.093 --> 01:52.686
My demands
on those closest to me can

01:52.688 --> 01:53.928
take a toll,
like --

01:53.930 --> 01:55.339
He was doing his job.

01:55.341 --> 01:57.449
Your father was a bodyguard,
not a bill collector.

01:57.451 --> 01:59.860
I sent him to Edgartown
to collect rent

01:59.862 --> 02:01.862
because I knew he would
treat people with dignity,

02:01.864 --> 02:03.347
and he lost
his life.

02:03.349 --> 02:04.772
I know the story.

02:04.774 --> 02:06.792
Someone high out of their mind
shot him on the front step

02:06.794 --> 02:08.443
for serving
an eviction notice.

02:08.445 --> 02:10.704
I sent<i> you</i>
to spy on Angela

02:10.706 --> 02:12.113
because I trusted you.

02:12.115 --> 02:15.692
Trust means
a great deal to me,

02:15.694 --> 02:19.696
especially if you're seeing
my daughter.

02:19.698 --> 02:21.198
[ Laughs ]

02:21.200 --> 02:24.368
You know,
if she has trust in you,

02:24.370 --> 02:26.370
one day,
she will come

02:26.372 --> 02:29.314
and place
her trust in me.

02:29.316 --> 02:30.557
[ Scoffs ]

02:30.559 --> 02:32.893
Spying on Angela isn't a way
to gain her trust

02:32.895 --> 02:34.060
or get to know her.

02:34.062 --> 02:36.380
You've been absent
her whole life.

02:36.382 --> 02:37.564
You're right,
my boy.

02:37.566 --> 02:40.066
I'm going to give
Angela and Nikki

02:40.068 --> 02:43.053
a cotillion week
to remember.

02:43.055 --> 02:44.329
[ Chuckles ]

02:44.331 --> 02:45.813
♪♪

02:45.815 --> 02:47.649
♪ Head high ♪

02:47.651 --> 02:49.226
♪ Confident ♪

02:49.228 --> 02:50.894
♪ Strong mind ♪

02:50.896 --> 02:52.245
♪ Resilient ♪

02:52.247 --> 02:56.991
♪ You can't break me,
I was born to rise ♪

02:56.993 --> 03:00.161
♪ Our kind of people ♪

03:00.163 --> 03:03.682
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

03:03.684 --> 03:06.685
♪ Our kind of people ♪

03:06.687 --> 03:10.597
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

03:10.599 --> 03:14.234
♪♪

03:15.512 --> 03:21.700
♪♪

03:21.702 --> 03:23.927
It's the same deal
every time I go home.

03:23.929 --> 03:25.445
They make up
a whole list of --

03:25.447 --> 03:28.281
Okay, ladies, we have less than
48 hours to cotillion,

03:28.283 --> 03:30.692
and this is gonna be
the best cotillion yet.

03:30.694 --> 03:32.102
..."I have two Emmys

03:32.104 --> 03:34.195
and the highest-rated
news show on the air,"

03:34.197 --> 03:36.030
and my father sill
made me clean the fish.

03:36.032 --> 03:38.108
[ Laughter ]
Manicure be damned.

03:38.110 --> 03:40.126
Alex.
What brings you to Oak Bluffs?

03:40.128 --> 03:42.295
[ Sighs ]
Well, I haven't taken a break

03:42.297 --> 03:43.964
since
the Obama administration.

03:43.966 --> 03:46.040
So I decided to summer here
with friends,

03:46.042 --> 03:47.634
Graceties
from the Manhattan chapter.

03:47.636 --> 03:50.395
Well, you all are so lucky
to have found a rental,

03:50.397 --> 03:51.713
you know,
this late in the season.

03:51.715 --> 03:54.791
And just in time
for the Oak Bluffs Cotillion.

03:54.793 --> 03:56.050
Come to
think of it,

03:56.052 --> 03:58.570
last time I saw you
was at<i> your</i> cotillion.

03:58.572 --> 04:00.480
Well,
that was ages ago.

04:00.482 --> 04:01.406
Another lifetime.

04:01.408 --> 04:03.224
For those of you
who are unaware,

04:03.226 --> 04:05.986
Alex was married
to Raymond for...

04:05.988 --> 04:08.396
wait, did you guys make it
to 12 months?

04:08.398 --> 04:09.939
[ Chuckles ]

04:09.941 --> 04:11.416
Thank you
for the warm welcome.

04:11.418 --> 04:13.252
I know my presence
as a celebrity

04:13.254 --> 04:14.644
can be
a little daunting.

04:14.646 --> 04:16.813
You know what's
even more daunting?

04:16.815 --> 04:20.074
Trying to find last-minute glam
for the cotillion.

04:20.076 --> 04:22.486
20% off
for all Graceties

04:22.488 --> 04:24.930
and prospectives
at Eve's Crown.

04:24.932 --> 04:28.341
Where everybody gets treated
like a celebrity.

04:28.343 --> 04:29.917
♪♪

04:29.919 --> 04:31.511
Homegirl trying to start
some mess.

04:31.513 --> 04:32.662
Hmm.

04:32.664 --> 04:34.439
Thanks, but I can
clean my own house.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.500
Alright, Graceties,
I'm officially

04:36.502 --> 04:38.835
calling our meeting
to order.

04:38.837 --> 04:40.595
Shall we?

04:40.597 --> 04:50.580
♪♪

04:52.200 --> 04:53.441
Hey.

04:53.443 --> 04:54.367
Got you 911 text.

04:54.369 --> 04:56.186
What's happened?
Alex Rivera.

04:56.188 --> 04:57.687
She's in Oak Bluffs.

04:57.689 --> 04:58.964
Really?
Mm.

04:58.966 --> 05:00.632
Hmm.
She say what she's doing here?

05:00.634 --> 05:02.192
I don't know.
She's probably trying to glow up

05:02.194 --> 05:05.045
from that raggedy
Manhattan Graceties chapter.

05:05.047 --> 05:06.696
You know, I think
she's still salty

05:06.698 --> 05:08.974
that you chose a true marriage
instead of a mistake.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.201
I just hope that
that's the last we see of her

05:11.203 --> 05:12.644
because my plate
is already full

05:12.646 --> 05:15.296
with everything having to do
with the cotillion as it is.

05:15.298 --> 05:18.208
No, listen, she's probably
just trying to sip some rosé

05:18.210 --> 05:20.485
and floss
like the rest of the guests.

05:20.487 --> 05:21.653
Mm.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.805
I'm sure it's nothing.

05:23.807 --> 05:25.407
I hope you're right.

05:26.401 --> 05:29.161
[ Sighs ]

05:30.313 --> 05:32.238
♪ Drop top coupe,
throw the whip in gear ♪

05:32.240 --> 05:34.816
♪ Took a bag full of cash
like a souvenir, uh ♪

05:34.818 --> 05:36.409
♪ 211 and we outta here ♪

05:36.411 --> 05:38.653
♪ Put the pedal on the floor,
got the jakes in the... ♪

05:38.655 --> 05:40.672
You know, I thought
being the face of Eve's Crown

05:40.674 --> 05:44.343
would be a lot more glamor
and a lot less,

05:44.345 --> 05:46.494
"Hi,
welcome to Eve's Crown."

05:46.496 --> 05:48.755
You know, if these women
filled the food bank

05:48.757 --> 05:50.849
the way they're filling up
on free champagne,

05:50.851 --> 05:53.259
we would solve
world hunger.

05:53.261 --> 05:55.095
I feel like there
are 10 times more

05:55.097 --> 05:57.931
Black people on this island
than when we first got here.

05:57.933 --> 06:01.585
Including
Miss Alex Rivera.

06:01.587 --> 06:03.511
Well, now, you know that
I've been ear-hustling

06:03.513 --> 06:04.846
these broads
all morning,

06:04.848 --> 06:07.682
and apparently, when Raymond
and Alex were together,

06:07.684 --> 06:09.442
she wasn't
one of them.

06:09.444 --> 06:10.443
But now she is.

06:10.445 --> 06:11.703
Sort of.

06:11.705 --> 06:14.781
Yeah, it seems like
they only really count you in

06:14.783 --> 06:16.099
if you're born in.

06:16.101 --> 06:17.859
And what does that say
about you and Nikki?

06:17.861 --> 06:20.528
[ Chuckles ]
Is that why you're letting Teddy
stand in as the father

06:20.530 --> 06:21.863
for the
Father-Daughter dance?

06:21.865 --> 06:23.106
Teddy offered.

06:23.199 --> 06:25.233
I thought it would be
a great opportunity for Nikki

06:25.235 --> 06:26.459
to get to know him.

06:26.461 --> 06:28.202
I can read it
all over your face.

06:28.204 --> 06:30.630
How do you<i> really</i> feel
about your daddy

06:30.632 --> 06:31.798
taking her
to cotillion?

06:31.800 --> 06:32.949
Alright.

06:32.968 --> 06:34.951
I'm still trying to play
the nice daughter

06:34.953 --> 06:36.469
to find out
what happened to Mama,

06:36.471 --> 06:37.621
but I don't trust him.

06:37.623 --> 06:39.547
I just can't help
but feeling like

06:39.549 --> 06:41.900
he doesn't do anything
without an agenda.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.810
I may even
have some dirt

06:43.812 --> 06:45.795
on what he was up to
back in the day.

06:45.797 --> 06:48.798
Tyrique and I got his brother
Louis Franklin's journals

06:48.800 --> 06:51.468
from 1983 and 1984.

06:51.470 --> 06:54.154
You and Tyrique have been
working on this together?

06:54.156 --> 06:55.229
Mm-hmm.

06:55.231 --> 06:57.974
Ange, you are
in dangerous territory.

06:57.976 --> 07:00.401
I know.
For both of us.

07:00.403 --> 07:02.178
But I don't
have a choice.

07:02.180 --> 07:03.997
I have to find out
what Teddy was up to

07:03.999 --> 07:05.573
when my mama
was arrested,

07:05.575 --> 07:07.575
figure out
the connection between him

07:07.577 --> 07:09.911
and those drugs that were
being run in Edgartown.

07:09.913 --> 07:11.821
That's how
I'll clear her name.
Mom?

07:11.823 --> 07:14.081
Um,
I know it's busy,

07:14.083 --> 07:16.101
but I got a text
from Taylor.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.661
Something about cotillion.

07:17.663 --> 07:19.012
Can I go?

07:19.014 --> 07:21.998
Yeah,
you can go.
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

07:22.000 --> 07:25.110
Okay, Taylor, so we're at
the beach, clearly.

07:25.112 --> 07:27.779
Yes, but no peeking.
You're gonna love it.

07:27.781 --> 07:29.430
Oh, my --
It feels nice.

07:29.432 --> 07:31.024
Step over here.

07:31.026 --> 07:33.526
Give me your hands.
Take a big step.

07:33.528 --> 07:34.769
There you go.
Okay.

07:34.771 --> 07:36.680
Alright.
You ready?

07:36.682 --> 07:38.031
Okay.

07:38.033 --> 07:40.867
Oh -- What --
What is all this?

07:40.869 --> 07:46.039
Nicole Vaughn,
will you allow me the honor

07:46.041 --> 07:48.692
of escorting you
to the Oak Bluffs Cotillion?

07:48.694 --> 07:50.026
[ Chuckles ]

07:50.028 --> 07:52.620
You want to be my escort
to cotillion?

07:52.622 --> 07:53.788
Yes.

07:53.790 --> 07:55.699
Oh. Okay.

07:55.701 --> 07:57.050
Um...

07:57.052 --> 08:01.128
Well,
I would be honored.

08:01.130 --> 08:04.316
Okay, so, there's
one more surprise.

08:04.318 --> 08:06.485
The other debs thought
what Lauren did to you

08:06.487 --> 08:09.546
at the Claiming Ceremony
was foul,

08:09.548 --> 08:12.991
so we took a vote.

08:12.993 --> 08:14.400
Alright.

08:14.402 --> 08:16.995
Oh, my God.

08:16.997 --> 08:19.055
Taylor!

08:19.057 --> 08:21.558
♪♪

08:21.560 --> 08:24.077
"Most Congenial".

08:24.079 --> 08:28.064
Most Congenial reads
the "Letter to Fathers", right?

08:28.066 --> 08:29.007
[ Sniffles ]

08:29.009 --> 08:33.011
I know your dad
wasn't really around,

08:33.013 --> 08:35.255
and if you want to,
you don't have to.

08:35.257 --> 08:37.832
Oh, no, no.
I -- The debs chose me.

08:37.834 --> 08:39.592
Of -- Of course
I want to.

08:39.594 --> 08:40.927
Um...

08:40.929 --> 08:42.837
"If it feels nice,
roll the dice."

08:42.839 --> 08:44.672
That's what Mama Eve
used to say.

08:44.674 --> 08:46.432
So, uh...

08:46.434 --> 08:48.527
I guess
I'm reading a speech.

08:48.529 --> 08:51.012
And you're gonna give
a bomb speech.

08:51.014 --> 08:53.365
[ Laughs ]

08:53.367 --> 08:59.596
♪♪

08:59.598 --> 09:01.264
Teddy: Ah!

09:01.266 --> 09:02.189
Hi.

09:02.191 --> 09:05.359
Your shop is coming
along nicely.

09:05.361 --> 09:06.378
A-As your mentor,

09:06.380 --> 09:08.605
I could offer
some advice about marketing,

09:08.607 --> 09:10.774
but looks like
you have that covered.

09:10.776 --> 09:11.941
[ Chuckles ]

09:11.943 --> 09:14.110
I'm guessing you're here
for Nikki?

09:14.112 --> 09:15.278
Mm.

09:15.371 --> 09:18.039
I just want to make sure
that you standing with her

09:18.041 --> 09:22.209
for cotillion
isn't some game to you.

09:22.211 --> 09:24.563
My motives towards
my granddaughter

09:24.565 --> 09:25.897
are well-intentioned.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.957
I want to get to know her,
as I do you.

09:27.959 --> 09:29.809
I'm here bearing gifts.

09:29.811 --> 09:31.311
You can't buy
her affection.

09:31.313 --> 09:32.645
Mm.

09:32.647 --> 09:34.647
It's tradition.

09:34.649 --> 09:39.894
The father gives
the debutante daughter pearls.

09:39.896 --> 09:42.396
These pearls belonged
to my mother,

09:42.398 --> 09:43.731
given to her
by my father.

09:43.733 --> 09:46.585
I would like to include Nikki
in that lineage.

09:46.587 --> 09:48.661
♪♪

09:48.663 --> 09:50.905
As for you,
my gift --

09:50.907 --> 09:52.665
No,
I don't need your trinkets.

09:52.667 --> 09:54.426
Thank you.
No.

09:54.428 --> 09:55.576
It's a gesture.

09:55.578 --> 09:57.578
Something I'd like
to help you with.

09:57.580 --> 10:01.099
I received a letter
from a Nate Robinson.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.827
The media attention
and gossip

10:03.829 --> 10:06.162
compelled him
to reach out to me.

10:06.164 --> 10:09.590
He said that he was hurt
because he was not able

10:09.592 --> 10:11.258
to protect his daughter
from all of that.

10:11.260 --> 10:12.944
Here.
You can read it for yourself.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.004
It's --
It's all in there.

10:15.006 --> 10:16.764
And when
he explained

10:16.766 --> 10:19.100
the particulars
of his case,

10:19.102 --> 10:21.511
he's been passed over
for parole twice.

10:21.513 --> 10:22.879
Did you know that?

10:22.881 --> 10:27.867
And yet,
even behind bars,

10:27.869 --> 10:30.186
in a system
that failed him,

10:30.188 --> 10:34.357
Nate's heart and mind
are with you and Nikki.

10:34.359 --> 10:37.377
I'm compelled to answer
his cries for assistance.

10:37.379 --> 10:39.028
He asked you for help?
Mm-hmm.

10:39.030 --> 10:40.380
And I'm sure
I can do something.

10:40.382 --> 10:44.367
I mean, I've raised funds
for the Innocence Project.

10:44.369 --> 10:46.293
I'm connected to
the state's Attorney General.

10:46.295 --> 10:48.888
And this is the relationship
I want us to have --

10:48.890 --> 10:50.707
supporting one another.

10:50.709 --> 10:54.560
Us...
against the world.

10:54.562 --> 10:57.230
So, you're saying you could
get him out?

10:57.232 --> 10:59.232
Hmm.

10:59.234 --> 11:02.385
I-I mean,
I need time.

11:02.387 --> 11:03.811
Uh,
Nikki doesn't --

11:03.813 --> 11:05.163
I need
to prepare her first.

11:05.165 --> 11:08.241
It's not gonna
happen overnight, Angela.

11:08.243 --> 11:09.984
Um,
legal briefs,

11:09.986 --> 11:12.562
proper investigation,
hearings --

11:12.564 --> 11:13.897
it could take months.

11:13.899 --> 11:15.415
I need
to think about this.

11:15.417 --> 11:18.325
I'll wait until
you make a decision.

11:18.327 --> 11:21.921
I can't give you back
the years lost between us,

11:21.923 --> 11:24.057
but perhaps
I can give Nikki

11:24.059 --> 11:26.092
a few years
with her father.

11:26.094 --> 11:28.669
As for you...

11:28.671 --> 11:34.341
I'm very happy
with you and Tyrique.

11:34.343 --> 11:37.587
♪♪

11:37.589 --> 11:38.697
He's a good man.

11:38.699 --> 11:43.118
♪♪

11:46.932 --> 11:53.712
♪ Baby, I remember when
loving was easy ♪

11:53.714 --> 11:56.030
♪♪

11:56.032 --> 11:57.607
Oh, no.

11:57.609 --> 11:59.384
You are not just
gonna lay around.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.611
And your room is a mess,
by the way.

12:01.613 --> 12:02.795
Mom.

12:02.797 --> 12:05.448
I don't
want those open.

12:05.450 --> 12:07.708
There will be
other Taylors.

12:07.710 --> 12:09.227
There's only one you.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.213
And I wish you would
value yourself a bit more.

12:12.215 --> 12:14.140
Now, get up.
A Dupont is never late.

12:14.142 --> 12:15.549
Late for what?

12:15.551 --> 12:16.717
Work. What?

12:16.719 --> 12:17.961
You're the one
who decided

12:17.963 --> 12:19.145
to get yourself
kicked out of cotillion.

12:19.147 --> 12:20.797
Now you get to spend
the rest of the summer

12:20.799 --> 12:23.057
deciding what you want to do
with the rest of your life.

12:23.059 --> 12:25.726
Now, get up.
Come on, Lauren.

12:25.728 --> 12:27.637
You got 15 minutes.

12:27.639 --> 12:29.973
♪♪

12:29.975 --> 12:32.992
Hey.

12:32.994 --> 12:36.162
You told Teddy
about us?

12:36.164 --> 12:38.164
He already knew.

12:38.166 --> 12:40.166
He saw us
leaving his office together,

12:40.168 --> 12:43.152
but I don't think he knows
we took those journals.

12:43.154 --> 12:46.097
Well, I skimmed them,
and I didn't see anything

12:46.099 --> 12:48.674
about my mom
or about Teddy dealing drugs,

12:48.676 --> 12:51.828
but I did see something
in this one about a Calvin.

12:51.830 --> 12:53.997
That's your dad,
right?

12:53.999 --> 12:55.832
Why would my dad be
in Louis' journals?

12:55.834 --> 12:58.017
He only
worked for Teddy.

12:58.019 --> 12:59.185
What's wrong?

12:59.279 --> 13:01.671
You seem like you got
something else on your mind.

13:01.673 --> 13:04.674
[ Sighs ]

13:04.676 --> 13:06.359
It's Nikki's father.

13:06.361 --> 13:07.952
Nate.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.530
Teddy offered to get him
out of prison.

13:10.532 --> 13:11.772
Just like that.

13:11.774 --> 13:14.459
Like he was deciding
what to order for dinner.

13:14.461 --> 13:15.627
Is that a bad thing?

13:15.629 --> 13:17.703
Tyrique,
I've thought a lot

13:17.705 --> 13:19.205
about Nate getting out

13:19.207 --> 13:21.448
so Nikki could have
a relationship with him,

13:21.450 --> 13:24.803
but just now,
all of a sudden

13:24.805 --> 13:26.971
because I'm a Franklin,

13:26.973 --> 13:29.048
his freedom is
a phone call away?

13:29.050 --> 13:31.810
It just feels like --
not cheating,

13:31.812 --> 13:33.144
but, like, what about

13:33.146 --> 13:35.480
all the other Black men
in prison wrongfully,

13:35.482 --> 13:38.558
unfair sentences,
who don't have a Teddy Franklin?

13:38.560 --> 13:39.725
Teddy took me in

13:39.727 --> 13:41.561
and changed
the course of my life.

13:41.563 --> 13:43.470
For a while,
he made my father's death

13:43.472 --> 13:44.972
feel like
hitting the lottery,

13:44.974 --> 13:46.716
and I-I struggled
with that.

13:46.718 --> 13:47.992
But then
I-I realized

13:47.994 --> 13:50.219
Teddy was trying
to do right by me.

13:50.221 --> 13:52.388
I think he's trying to do
the same for you and Nikki.

13:52.390 --> 13:54.223
Take the access
he has.

13:54.225 --> 13:57.393
Then find a way
to pay it forward.

13:57.395 --> 13:58.652
♪♪

13:58.654 --> 14:01.172
Why are you
so amazing?

14:01.174 --> 14:04.676
Campaigning for your woman's
baby daddy.

14:04.678 --> 14:08.921
Have you thought about what's
gonna happen when he gets out?

14:08.923 --> 14:10.923
You have
nothing to worry about.

14:10.925 --> 14:13.593
I'm right
where I want to be.

14:13.595 --> 14:20.692
♪♪

14:21.920 --> 14:24.988
Um, can you give me a moment,
please?

14:32.430 --> 14:33.930
Daddy,
we need to talk.

14:33.932 --> 14:35.431
Can you give us the room,
please?

14:35.433 --> 14:36.523
Thanks.

14:36.525 --> 14:37.858
Will you be able
to present

14:37.860 --> 14:39.193
the "Letter to Daughters"
tomorrow?

14:39.195 --> 14:41.379
I'm -- I'm just concerned
about your condition,

14:41.381 --> 14:43.106
and after the fall --
I'm fine.

14:43.108 --> 14:45.274
Besides, we have greater things
to worry about.

14:45.276 --> 14:47.126
You were right
about Tyrique.
Mm.

14:47.128 --> 14:48.961
So he did
cut the camera.

14:48.963 --> 14:50.221
And he's seeing Angela.

14:50.223 --> 14:52.539
He lied to me, which is
a ship that I have to right,

14:52.541 --> 14:54.893
as well as my relationship
with Angela,

14:54.895 --> 14:56.394
which is why
I'm going to help

14:56.396 --> 14:58.897
Nikki's father
get out of prison.

14:58.899 --> 15:00.306
♪♪

15:00.308 --> 15:01.474
Prison?

15:01.476 --> 15:02.400
Her ex wrote me,

15:02.402 --> 15:05.570
and now
I have an opportunity

15:05.572 --> 15:08.131
that I'm going to use
to my advantage.

15:08.133 --> 15:10.057
To break up
Angela and Tyrique?

15:10.059 --> 15:11.558
Mm-hmm.

15:11.560 --> 15:13.394
Daddy,
come on.

15:13.396 --> 15:15.562
These are people we're
talking about, not chess pieces.

15:15.564 --> 15:16.897
I'm helping!

15:16.899 --> 15:18.399
And when
it all works out,

15:18.401 --> 15:19.976
I'll be
the kindly patron,

15:19.978 --> 15:21.811
the Vaughns
will be reunited,

15:21.813 --> 15:22.903
I will
get my soldier back,

15:22.905 --> 15:25.164
Franklin Holdings
will receive great PR,

15:25.166 --> 15:28.651
and the stadium deal
could use a fresh coat

15:28.653 --> 15:29.986
of "Innocence Project" paint

15:29.988 --> 15:33.339
to cover up the scuffs
we've accumulated along the way.

15:33.341 --> 15:34.265
Hmm.

15:34.267 --> 15:35.825
Well, you might want
to double coat

15:35.827 --> 15:38.828
the scuffs before Raymond's ex
comes knocking.

15:38.830 --> 15:40.179
She's summering
in the Bluffs,

15:40.181 --> 15:42.014
and she will keep her ear
close to the ground.

15:42.016 --> 15:43.015
[ Sighs ]

15:43.017 --> 15:44.591
The last thing
I need right now

15:44.593 --> 15:46.945
is Alex to take notes
during cotillion.

15:46.947 --> 15:48.595
I mean, Olivia already wants
my head on a platter

15:48.597 --> 15:51.857
after Lauren's stunt
at the Claiming Ceremony.

15:51.859 --> 15:53.192
The cotillion
has to be perfect.

15:53.194 --> 15:55.861
Then we give Alex
nothing to report.

15:55.863 --> 15:58.957
I know how much
this weekend means to you.

15:58.959 --> 16:01.626
We're always talking
about<i> my</i> legacy.

16:01.628 --> 16:04.020
The cotillion could be
the beginning of<i> yours.</i>

16:04.022 --> 16:06.522
And it
has always been

16:06.524 --> 16:11.861
me and you...
against the world.

16:11.863 --> 16:15.098
Me and you,
against the world.

16:15.867 --> 16:17.366
[ Sighs ]
[ Laughs ]

16:17.368 --> 16:19.460
Mm.

16:19.462 --> 16:20.979
Take care of yourself,
Daddy.

16:20.981 --> 16:22.463
I will.

16:22.465 --> 16:24.557
Okay.

16:24.559 --> 16:27.226
Jimmy!

16:27.228 --> 16:28.561
Mm.

16:28.563 --> 16:31.230
Vacation's always better
with bubbles.

16:31.232 --> 16:32.639
Care for a glass?

16:32.641 --> 16:33.807
Oh, relax.

16:33.809 --> 16:35.551
My housemates
have gone into town.

16:35.553 --> 16:36.494
No one will see you.

16:36.496 --> 16:38.830
Yet you show up, uninvited,
at my house,

16:38.832 --> 16:39.998
and let everyone
on the island

16:40.000 --> 16:42.649
see that you're here
for the entire summer?

16:42.651 --> 16:44.227
♪♪

16:44.229 --> 16:45.986
You asked me to look into
Teddy Franklin.

16:45.988 --> 16:47.396
I can do that best
right here,

16:47.398 --> 16:48.673
where he lives
and breathes.

16:48.675 --> 16:51.658
But I need you to do that
without stirring up the past.

16:51.660 --> 16:55.162
♪♪

16:55.164 --> 16:58.758
So, Leah doesn't know
you married your rebound?

16:58.760 --> 17:01.019
♪♪

17:01.021 --> 17:03.095
It may have
started that way,

17:03.097 --> 17:05.523
but Leah and I
are very much in love.

17:05.525 --> 17:07.641
Just do your job
and keep my wife out of it.

17:07.643 --> 17:08.934
Clear?

17:08.936 --> 17:10.603
Crystal.

17:10.605 --> 17:15.992
♪♪

17:20.098 --> 17:26.602
♪♪

17:26.604 --> 17:27.937
[ Both laugh ]

17:27.939 --> 17:29.939
How about that?

17:29.941 --> 17:31.031
You're a natural.

17:31.033 --> 17:32.958
You take lessons
when you were younger?

17:32.960 --> 17:34.052
No.

17:34.054 --> 17:35.961
Um, actually,
Mama Eve taught me.

17:35.963 --> 17:38.389
Yeah, she was
a really good dancer.

17:38.391 --> 17:39.706
She was.

17:39.708 --> 17:43.061
I hope my escorting you
would have made her happy.

17:44.956 --> 17:46.956
We have much work to do
to get acquainted.

17:46.958 --> 17:50.960
Um,
if there is anything --

17:50.962 --> 17:57.483
um, advice,
an answer, an ear --

17:57.485 --> 17:59.652
I'm here.

17:59.654 --> 18:02.896
Thanks.

18:02.898 --> 18:06.584
Actually, um...
I have to read

18:06.586 --> 18:09.478
"A Letter to Fathers"
at the cotillion,

18:09.480 --> 18:12.573
and...
that's just something

18:12.575 --> 18:14.741
I don't really know
anything about.

18:14.743 --> 18:15.835
I actually looked up

18:15.837 --> 18:18.487
a few of your TED Talks
for pointers.

18:18.489 --> 18:19.822
[ Laughs ]

18:19.824 --> 18:22.916
Well, um,
to combat<i> my</i> nerves,

18:22.918 --> 18:24.994
I carry
an antique coin

18:24.996 --> 18:27.163
given to me
by my great-grandfather,

18:27.165 --> 18:29.665
who stood
next to Frederick Douglass

18:29.667 --> 18:31.758
to talk about freedom.

18:31.760 --> 18:33.444
It reminds me
that I come from

18:33.446 --> 18:37.173
a very long line
of brilliant orators.

18:37.175 --> 18:38.765
And so do you.

18:38.767 --> 18:40.176
Thank you.

18:40.178 --> 18:42.787
You're welcome.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.623
So, I will
see you tomorrow?

18:45.625 --> 18:47.683
Wouldn't miss it.

18:47.685 --> 18:49.460
♪♪

18:49.462 --> 18:52.296
Oh! [ Chuckles ]

18:52.298 --> 18:54.966
Bye.
Bye.

18:54.968 --> 18:59.637
♪♪

18:59.639 --> 19:01.030
Hi.

19:01.032 --> 19:04.124
Um, Nikki, I wanted
to apologize to you

19:04.126 --> 19:07.036
for what I did to you
at the Claiming Ceremony.

19:07.038 --> 19:08.721
Sorry.

19:08.723 --> 19:11.965
Actually, I owe you
an apology, too, Lauren.

19:11.967 --> 19:13.985
I didn't mean to hurt you
with Taylor.

19:13.987 --> 19:15.135
I-It's cool.

19:15.137 --> 19:16.970
I mean, she gave me
a ton of chances,

19:16.972 --> 19:18.305
and I just
ruined them all,

19:18.307 --> 19:19.565
and then
I took it out on you,

19:19.567 --> 19:20.992
and now I'm making up for it
because my mother

19:20.994 --> 19:22.827
is making you work
all summer, so...

19:22.829 --> 19:24.720
Don't chip a nail,
princess.

19:24.722 --> 19:27.890
Well, I'd rather break a nail
than be broken, so...

19:27.892 --> 19:30.668
Have fun
at the cotillion.

19:30.670 --> 19:32.745
I really do
mean that.

19:32.747 --> 19:36.899
♪♪

19:36.901 --> 19:38.992
♪ Ooh ♪

19:38.994 --> 19:40.403
[ Sighs ]

19:40.405 --> 19:41.995
♪ Ooh ♪

19:41.997 --> 19:43.756
Angela: Y'all do not play
about cotillion.

19:43.758 --> 19:45.424
Uh, no,
we do not.

19:45.426 --> 19:48.427
Well, this is
a perfect color match.

19:48.429 --> 19:49.929
I've got the clippings
right here.

19:49.931 --> 19:52.190
Pop it in, extra volume,
you're good.

19:52.192 --> 19:54.600
Okay.
For volume.

19:54.602 --> 19:56.919
Uh, 20% off,
right?

19:56.921 --> 19:58.863
Well, how do you think
I stay wealthy?

19:58.865 --> 19:59.864
Okay.

19:59.866 --> 20:01.699
Just taking notes.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.426
♪♪

20:03.428 --> 20:05.928
I hope you don't mind,
but my father told me

20:05.930 --> 20:08.873
about Nikki's father,
and I'm sorry that you both

20:08.875 --> 20:11.600
had to go through
something so difficult.

20:11.602 --> 20:14.937
But I assure you,
if anyone can help,

20:14.939 --> 20:16.530
Teddy Franklin can.

20:16.532 --> 20:19.775
Listen, please do not
say anything to Nikki.

20:19.777 --> 20:21.201
She knows
nothing about this.

20:21.203 --> 20:22.553
I do not --
Trust me.

20:22.555 --> 20:25.281
I know things with an ex
can be tricky,

20:25.283 --> 20:27.450
and I wouldn't
hurt Nikki.
Good.

20:27.452 --> 20:30.286
'Cause I wouldn't want to have
to take out my Boston on you.

20:30.288 --> 20:31.787
Oh.
Yeah, please don't do that,

20:31.789 --> 20:33.046
because something
tells me

20:33.048 --> 20:35.733
that your Boston
would likely --

20:35.735 --> 20:37.993
likely beat
my bougie ass.

20:37.995 --> 20:39.052
Up and down
the street.

20:39.054 --> 20:41.054
Okay?
[ Both laugh ]

20:41.056 --> 20:42.389
Woman: Thank you.
Thank you.

20:42.391 --> 20:45.726
Honestly, I feel guilty
accepting Teddy's help.

20:45.728 --> 20:48.821
It's like
he's doing too much.

20:48.823 --> 20:50.155
He made
this speech about

20:50.157 --> 20:52.065
it being us
against the world,

20:52.067 --> 20:53.584
and it's like,
man...

20:53.586 --> 20:56.161
Wait -- Wait, he --
he said that to you?

20:56.163 --> 20:58.664
I know he's trying to make up
for lost time,

20:58.666 --> 20:59.815
but it's too much.

20:59.817 --> 21:01.817
It's too soon.
Yeah.

21:01.819 --> 21:03.928
Well,
America's justice system

21:03.930 --> 21:05.838
has never favored
Black people,

21:05.840 --> 21:07.506
whether we're wealthy
or poor.

21:07.508 --> 21:11.269
So, helping Nate is a move
toward solidarity.

21:11.271 --> 21:12.828
[ Cellphone rings ]
For all of us.

21:12.830 --> 21:14.997
Oh. Uh. Oh.
I have to take this.

21:14.999 --> 21:16.165
Oh, yeah, well,
I've gotta go.

21:16.167 --> 21:18.609
I've got some seating charts
to review.

21:18.611 --> 21:20.260
Thank you for this.
Yeah.

21:20.262 --> 21:23.614
<i> This is a pre-paid collect call</i>
<i> from an inmate at...</i>

21:23.616 --> 21:25.190
Angela:<i> Hi.</i>

21:25.192 --> 21:27.176
I-I'm sorry to be calling you
like this, but --

21:27.178 --> 21:28.527
<i> Teddy showed me</i>
<i> your letter.</i>

21:28.529 --> 21:30.863
<i> Says your case</i>
<i> is up for review.</i>

21:30.865 --> 21:32.456
That's --
That's not why I did it.

21:32.458 --> 21:34.792
I-I wanted to make sure
Nikki was protected.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.443
<i> But if</i>
<i> he's gonna help --</i>

21:36.445 --> 21:39.371
He says all I have to do
is say the word and it's done.

21:39.373 --> 21:40.539
So,
what's the word, Gee?

21:40.541 --> 21:42.115
<i> The word is</i>
<i> I got to think about</i>

21:42.117 --> 21:44.360
<i> how all of this</i>
<i> will affect Nikki.</i>

21:44.362 --> 21:45.361
[ Sighs ]

21:45.363 --> 21:47.530
I don't want it
to seem like

21:47.532 --> 21:49.698
I'm trying to keep you
in prison,

21:49.700 --> 21:51.309
but I feel like

21:51.311 --> 21:54.203
Teddy's trying
to buy my love.

21:54.205 --> 21:57.039
If writing your father
gets me out of here,

21:57.041 --> 22:00.376
to meet my daughter
and get back what I lost,

22:00.378 --> 22:02.394
I-I'll take
that chance.

22:02.396 --> 22:04.229
<i> That man</i>
<i> is your father.</i>

22:04.231 --> 22:05.489
<i> He wants</i>
<i> another shot,</i>

22:05.491 --> 22:07.307
<i> and you hold</i>
<i> his fate in your hands.</i>

22:07.309 --> 22:10.386
<i> When you gonna let</i>
<i> Teddy Franklin out of jail?</i>

22:10.388 --> 22:20.396
♪♪

22:20.398 --> 22:22.064
♪♪

22:22.066 --> 22:25.593
Oh, not too hot,
please.

22:27.496 --> 22:28.737
Ow!

22:28.739 --> 22:30.997
I said
not too hot.

22:30.999 --> 22:31.998
♪♪

22:32.000 --> 22:34.593
You violated our agreement,
Alex.

22:34.595 --> 22:35.761
How did you
get in here?

22:35.763 --> 22:37.930
Money grants access,
dear.

22:37.932 --> 22:41.083
Isn't that why
you've worked so hard,

22:41.085 --> 22:43.919
to go
from fisherman's daughter

22:43.921 --> 22:46.589
to
financial news anchor?

22:46.591 --> 22:49.367
The deal was
I couldn't reach out to Raymond.

22:49.369 --> 22:51.702
I didn't.
<i> He</i> reached out to<i> me.</i>

22:51.704 --> 22:53.596
I told you once --

22:53.598 --> 22:57.433
stay away
from my family.

22:57.435 --> 22:59.025
I don't like
repeating myself.

22:59.027 --> 23:00.544
I'm not
scared of you anymore.

23:00.546 --> 23:03.530
That's because I'm not
trying to scare you.

23:03.532 --> 23:05.624
Yet.

23:05.626 --> 23:09.870
You know, this spa
has very nice showers.

23:09.872 --> 23:11.947
You should try one.

23:11.949 --> 23:14.558
Smelling a little fishy
in here.

23:14.560 --> 23:16.301
[ Gasps ]

23:16.303 --> 23:24.652
♪♪

23:30.726 --> 23:33.244
You were good to me once.

23:36.249 --> 23:38.082
Uh,
what's this is hear

23:38.084 --> 23:40.993
that you're
starting a charity?

23:40.995 --> 23:43.996
Nikki just didn't have
the same advantages as I do,

23:43.998 --> 23:45.572
and I kinda used that
to hurt her.

23:45.574 --> 23:48.759
I just want to be better,
you know?

23:48.761 --> 23:50.243
I mean,
something more than

23:50.245 --> 23:54.339
running office errands
at Franklin Holdings.

23:54.341 --> 23:55.599
Don't be mad.

23:55.601 --> 23:58.677
I'm not.
Now, come on.

23:58.679 --> 24:00.104
Tell me about this.
Okay.

24:00.106 --> 24:02.181
So, it's called
"Lauren's Closet".

24:02.183 --> 24:03.348
Mm-hmm.

24:03.501 --> 24:05.091
And I am donating my wardrobe
to young women

24:05.093 --> 24:07.060
who need professional clothing
that can't afford it.

24:07.062 --> 24:08.595
Mom, it's actually
really taken off.

24:08.597 --> 24:10.931
Like, all of my followers
have gotten involved.

24:10.933 --> 24:13.993
[ Chuckles ] Wow.
That's impressive.

24:16.180 --> 24:18.414
I hope you're not
giving that one away.

24:21.352 --> 24:24.295
I don't really know
what to do with it.

24:24.297 --> 24:26.130
Well, I think maybe you
should just wear it.

24:26.132 --> 24:29.041
You've clearly
risen above your mistakes,

24:29.043 --> 24:31.026
which is what I told
the Graceties

24:31.028 --> 24:33.545
when I went
to plead your case.

24:33.547 --> 24:35.698
Seriously?
Mm-hmm.

24:35.700 --> 24:37.049
Oh!
[ Laughs ]

24:37.051 --> 24:39.626
Welcome back
to cotillion, baby.

24:39.628 --> 24:40.794
Thank you,
Mommy.

24:40.796 --> 24:42.371
Mm-hmm.

24:42.373 --> 24:46.817
♪♪

24:46.819 --> 24:48.152
[ Laughs ]
Excuse me, everyone.

24:48.154 --> 24:49.561
May I have your attention?

24:49.714 --> 24:52.973
I just wanted to thank you all
for coming to celebrate

24:52.975 --> 24:55.493
my first cotillion
as president.

24:55.495 --> 24:58.329
[ Chuckles ]
To the first of many.

24:59.390 --> 25:06.170
♪♪

25:06.172 --> 25:07.654
Mm.

25:07.656 --> 25:11.658
Angela, Patricia,
you both look exquisite.

25:11.660 --> 25:12.918
Thank you.
Thank you.

25:12.920 --> 25:14.903
I'm moving you
to the family table.

25:14.905 --> 25:16.162
Oh.
Here.

25:16.164 --> 25:17.256
New table cards.

25:17.258 --> 25:19.591
Well, enjoy cotillion,
Miss...

25:19.593 --> 25:21.685
Aunt Piggy,
Aunt Angela.

25:21.687 --> 25:24.355
Thank you,
Quincy.

25:24.357 --> 25:25.931
[ Chuckles ]

25:25.933 --> 25:28.083
Oh.
Table One.

25:28.085 --> 25:30.528
So, the Franklins get
the best seats in the house.

25:30.530 --> 25:31.695
Yes.

25:31.697 --> 25:34.273
And everyone
will be watching.

25:34.275 --> 25:36.867
♪♪

25:36.869 --> 25:38.761
You know,
I think I could use

25:38.763 --> 25:40.704
a glass
of bubbly myself.

25:40.706 --> 25:42.281
Could you
grab one for me?

25:42.283 --> 25:44.357
I'll get you.
[ Chuckles ]

25:44.359 --> 25:46.377
And just
what are you up to

25:46.379 --> 25:48.620
with all this
Nate business?

25:48.622 --> 25:50.864
I don't trust you

25:50.866 --> 25:53.033
as far
as I can throw you.

25:53.035 --> 25:54.126
[ Chuckles ]

25:54.128 --> 25:55.719
Well,
instead of focusing on me,

25:55.721 --> 25:57.037
worry about yourself.

25:57.039 --> 25:59.131
You know, I was surprised
to see you here.

25:59.133 --> 26:02.709
I'm sure someone
on this old staff

26:02.711 --> 26:03.894
will recognize you

26:03.896 --> 26:06.046
from back in
the old days.

26:06.048 --> 26:08.140
Loyalty keeps them
from spilling<i> my</i> secrets.

26:08.142 --> 26:10.626
What keeps them
from spilling<i> yours?</i>

26:10.628 --> 26:12.570
♪♪

26:12.572 --> 26:14.071
I'm sorry.
I better go.

26:14.073 --> 26:16.632
I have a very special deb
to escort.

26:16.634 --> 26:17.966
[ Chuckles ]

26:17.968 --> 26:20.393
Well,
he's trying, I guess.

26:20.395 --> 26:22.471
♪♪

26:22.473 --> 26:23.581
You okay?

26:23.583 --> 26:25.732
You know what?

26:25.734 --> 26:28.143
I just knew that I would be able
to push through tonight,

26:28.145 --> 26:30.979
but I'm having another one
of my terrible headaches,

26:30.981 --> 26:32.497
and I don't want
to ruin it for Nikki.

26:32.499 --> 26:35.075
So, can you please
tell baby girl

26:35.077 --> 26:36.409
that I am so sorry,

26:36.411 --> 26:39.671
and you make sure that you take
lots of videos, okay?

26:39.673 --> 26:42.658
Alright, sorry, I'm out
of this Mickey flick.

26:42.660 --> 26:44.435
Feel better.

26:44.437 --> 26:53.502
♪♪

26:53.504 --> 26:54.594
♪♪

26:54.596 --> 26:56.763
Honey, you should
head over to cotillion.

26:56.765 --> 26:59.265
♪♪

26:59.267 --> 27:02.027
This cocktail hour
is for friends and family.

27:02.029 --> 27:04.437
I must have overlooked
inviting you.

27:04.439 --> 27:06.031
I heard some Graceties
chattering,

27:06.033 --> 27:07.850
and I thought
it was open to all.

27:07.852 --> 27:09.960
Though you should have seen
the glare I got from Olivia

27:09.962 --> 27:11.854
as I signed
the guest book.

27:11.856 --> 27:13.464
She's not a fan.

27:13.466 --> 27:14.706
Oh?

27:14.708 --> 27:16.783
Why would you
say that?

27:16.785 --> 27:19.044
She's had a grudge
against me,

27:19.046 --> 27:20.620
ever since...

27:20.622 --> 27:22.806
I'm sure you know the way
I broke Raymond's heart

27:22.808 --> 27:24.290
didn't sit well
with her.

27:24.292 --> 27:26.459
Leaving a "Dear John"
letter was...

27:26.461 --> 27:29.462
what was
the word she used?

27:29.464 --> 27:31.482
"Corriente".

27:31.484 --> 27:33.633
A "Dear John" letter...

27:33.635 --> 27:37.971
would definitely
rub Olivia the wrong way.

27:37.973 --> 27:40.732
Excuse me.
I have guests to attend to.

27:40.734 --> 27:46.738
♪♪

27:46.740 --> 27:48.481
Olivia:
Ladies and gentlemen,

27:48.483 --> 27:51.560
our debutantes
and their escorts.

27:51.562 --> 27:56.423
[ Applause ]

28:04.258 --> 28:13.673
♪♪

28:13.675 --> 28:15.250
♪♪

28:15.252 --> 28:16.860
[<i> Hip-hop music plays</i> ]
Alright, alright, listen up.

28:16.862 --> 28:19.588
You're always telling us to
be the change we want to see.

28:19.590 --> 28:21.089
Well, this is it.

28:21.091 --> 28:22.849
♪♪

28:22.851 --> 28:25.018
[ Applause ]

28:25.020 --> 28:28.706
♪♪

28:28.708 --> 28:32.525
[ Cheers and applause ]

28:32.527 --> 28:38.698
♪♪

28:38.700 --> 28:41.218
[ Cheers and applause ]

28:41.220 --> 28:50.561
♪♪

28:50.563 --> 28:59.052
♪♪

28:59.054 --> 29:00.796
[ Clears throat ]

29:00.798 --> 29:04.299
Sorry.

29:04.301 --> 29:07.469
[ Indistinct shouting ]

29:07.471 --> 29:10.581
♪♪

29:10.583 --> 29:14.734
Man: Hey, debs and gents 2021
in the building.

29:14.736 --> 29:17.045
[ Cheers and applause ]

29:19.817 --> 29:23.502
Well,
that was quite unexpected.

29:23.504 --> 29:25.262
[ Laughs ]

29:25.264 --> 29:28.081
Now,
ladies and gentlemen,

29:28.083 --> 29:31.493
as your outgoing
chapter president,

29:31.495 --> 29:36.681
it is my pleasure to deliver
this evening's opening remarks.

29:36.683 --> 29:41.094
I'd like to start by saying
this has always been

29:41.096 --> 29:43.781
my favorite event of the year.

29:43.783 --> 29:47.692
It's the time when
the families of Oak Bluffs

29:47.694 --> 29:49.620
come together in celebration

29:49.622 --> 29:53.015
of the next generation
of stellar young ladies.

29:53.017 --> 29:55.017
<i> Alex</i> dumped<i> you?</i>

29:55.019 --> 29:57.628
Our entire marriage,
I thought you chose me

29:57.630 --> 29:58.962
because you loved me.

29:58.964 --> 30:01.540
And now I found out
I'm the consolation prize?

30:01.542 --> 30:04.192
Why would she say that to me
except to hurt me?

30:04.194 --> 30:05.193
I'm with
the right woman, Leah.

30:05.195 --> 30:08.305
It doesn't matter
how we got here.

30:08.307 --> 30:09.473
♪♪

30:09.475 --> 30:11.533
It matters to<i> me.</i>

30:11.535 --> 30:13.626
I want her gone.

30:13.628 --> 30:14.719
Now.

30:14.872 --> 30:17.463
And if I have to do it,
it won't be pretty.

30:17.465 --> 30:26.657
♪♪

30:30.721 --> 30:33.831
[ Crickets chirping ]

30:33.833 --> 30:38.727
"Calvin Chapman was found
in his car, shot in the head.

30:38.729 --> 30:40.745
What has Teddy done?"

30:40.747 --> 30:42.064
<i> I know the story.</i>

30:42.066 --> 30:43.489
<i> Someone high out of their mind</i>
<i> shot him</i>

30:43.491 --> 30:46.326
<i> on their front step</i>
<i> for serving an eviction notice.</i>

30:46.328 --> 30:53.925
♪♪

30:53.927 --> 30:56.353
[ Cellphone clicks ]

30:56.355 --> 30:59.097
[ Ringing ]

30:59.099 --> 31:02.192
<i> At the tone,</i>
<i> please record your message.</i>

31:02.194 --> 31:04.027
Angela, call me back.

31:04.029 --> 31:07.089
I think Teddy's been lying
about how my father died.

31:07.091 --> 31:08.699
♪♪

31:08.701 --> 31:12.427
Olivia:
You are our blessings.

31:12.429 --> 31:14.262
[ Applause ]

31:14.264 --> 31:16.948
Champagne, please.

31:16.950 --> 31:19.359
Uh,
he'll have a water.

31:19.361 --> 31:20.452
[ Scoffs ]

31:20.454 --> 31:22.045
You ready for
"Letter to Daughters"?

31:22.047 --> 31:24.606
Mm-hmm.
Steady as a rock.

31:24.608 --> 31:25.941
[ Both laugh ]

31:25.943 --> 31:28.610
Olivia:
...Leah Franklin-Dupont.

31:28.612 --> 31:30.462
Oh.

31:30.464 --> 31:32.464
There's your cue
to introduce me.

31:32.466 --> 31:35.434
[ Applause ]

31:46.405 --> 31:48.797
Good evening, everyone,
and thank you, Olivia,

31:48.799 --> 31:53.076
for your decades of service
and amazing leadership.

31:53.078 --> 31:55.303
On the night
of my debutante ball,

31:55.305 --> 31:58.231
my father delivered
the "Letter to Daughters".

31:58.233 --> 32:02.811
20 years later, to once again
bless us with his wisdom,

32:02.813 --> 32:05.071
my father, Mr. Teddy Franklin.

32:05.073 --> 32:08.258
[ Applause ]

32:15.417 --> 32:17.417
Thank you.

32:17.419 --> 32:27.427
♪♪

32:27.429 --> 32:33.599
♪♪

32:33.601 --> 32:38.513
With daughters, a father's role
comes with added responsibility.

32:38.515 --> 32:43.243
You are the one she comes to
in fear, in confidence,

32:43.245 --> 32:48.948
for advice,
to lean on at all times.

32:48.950 --> 32:54.137
But fathers sometimes
fall short.

32:54.139 --> 32:59.459
Angela Vaughn, my daughter,
you deserved better.

32:59.461 --> 33:05.557
I thought grand gestures could
sweep away years of inaction.

33:05.559 --> 33:10.395
I hope an apology gives us
a real start.

33:10.397 --> 33:13.381
Angela...

33:13.383 --> 33:16.017
I'm sorry.

33:16.019 --> 33:21.164
And now, our most
"Most Congenial" debutante

33:21.166 --> 33:25.818
will deliver
"Letters to Fathers".

33:25.820 --> 33:27.896
Nicole Vaughn.

33:27.898 --> 33:29.731
My granddaughter.

33:29.733 --> 33:31.591
[ Applause ]

33:36.015 --> 33:37.830
It's alright.

33:37.832 --> 33:41.852
♪♪

33:41.854 --> 33:44.596
Speak from the heart.

33:44.598 --> 33:51.603
♪♪

33:51.605 --> 33:54.364
[ Sighs ]

33:54.366 --> 33:57.425
I don't know what it's like
to have a father's love,

33:57.427 --> 34:01.429
but I was blessed to have
three amazing women in my life

34:01.431 --> 34:04.857
who made sure I had
everything I needed.

34:04.859 --> 34:09.880
Though all the fathers out there
deserve their thanks,

34:09.882 --> 34:11.773
my "Letter to Fathers"

34:11.775 --> 34:16.035
will send some love to all
the amazing mothers out there.

34:16.037 --> 34:17.370
Like mine.

34:17.372 --> 34:26.730
♪♪

34:26.732 --> 34:36.740
♪♪

34:36.742 --> 34:46.658
♪♪

34:46.660 --> 34:50.087
♪♪

34:50.089 --> 34:52.905
That bracelet
and that coin --

34:52.907 --> 34:55.425
they're both
family heirlooms.

34:55.427 --> 34:58.169
And I'm still not sure
I should have accepted them.

34:58.171 --> 35:00.913
Mm.
Be grateful.

35:00.915 --> 35:03.325
He's not always giving.

35:03.327 --> 35:05.009
♪♪

35:05.011 --> 35:06.419
Mademoiselle.

35:06.421 --> 35:08.179
Thank you.

35:08.181 --> 35:09.347
May I share a dance

35:09.349 --> 35:11.499
with another one
of my girls?

35:11.501 --> 35:13.351
Leah.

35:13.353 --> 35:22.694
♪♪

35:22.696 --> 35:23.862
♪♪

35:23.864 --> 35:26.623
You used
your entire speech

35:26.625 --> 35:28.366
to apologize
to Angela?

35:28.368 --> 35:31.386
I want
to win her trust.

35:31.388 --> 35:33.855
Public acknowledgement
of my missteps

35:33.857 --> 35:36.541
could help with that.

35:36.543 --> 35:38.877
What about my
public acknowledgement, Daddy?

35:38.879 --> 35:42.530
I mean,
the hoops I've jumped through

35:42.532 --> 35:45.124
covering for you.

35:45.126 --> 35:47.978
Lying to my husband
for you.

35:47.980 --> 35:49.462
Keeping your diagnosis
a secret.

35:49.464 --> 35:52.798
I mean, I'm the one
who supports and protects

35:52.800 --> 35:56.319
the great
Teddy Franklin.

35:56.321 --> 35:57.803
Not her.

35:57.805 --> 36:00.732
[ Voice breaking ] And then
I don't even get a mention

36:00.734 --> 36:02.734
in the
"Letter to Daughters"?

36:02.736 --> 36:05.495
If you want to spend the time
you have left with Angela,

36:05.497 --> 36:06.997
go ahead.

36:06.999 --> 36:09.148
I guess we'll just
share our last moment

36:09.150 --> 36:10.725
at your funeral.

36:10.727 --> 36:12.560
No.

36:12.562 --> 36:19.659
♪♪

36:19.661 --> 36:21.661
[ Cellphone clicks ]

36:21.663 --> 36:23.663
Teddy Franklin.

36:23.665 --> 36:33.673
♪♪

36:33.675 --> 36:37.027
♪♪

36:37.029 --> 36:40.422
[ Buzzer ]

36:40.424 --> 36:44.092
[ Chatter ]

36:44.094 --> 36:46.928
Robinson.
Let's go.

36:46.930 --> 36:48.354
Crack D-42!

36:48.356 --> 36:50.098
[ Buzzer, cell door opens ]

36:50.100 --> 36:56.546
♪♪

36:56.548 --> 36:59.123
♪<i> Ain't got time</i>
<i> for no comments</i> ♪

36:59.125 --> 37:01.051
♪<i> Only adding' paper</i>
<i> to the money clip</i> ♪

37:01.053 --> 37:04.128
♪<i> Stack it up to the ceiling</i> ♪

37:04.130 --> 37:07.224
♪<i> So I don't feel a thing</i>
<i> when I'm spendin' it</i> ♪

37:07.226 --> 37:08.374
♪♪

37:08.376 --> 37:10.452
I saw
what you did for Nikki.

37:10.454 --> 37:11.711
Oh.
Thank you.

37:11.713 --> 37:12.878
You're welcome.

37:12.880 --> 37:14.639
And I have
good news for you.

37:14.641 --> 37:16.641
Nate is
gonna be released.

37:16.643 --> 37:17.883
Released?
Mm-hmm.

37:17.885 --> 37:19.218
I spoke with
a few of my contacts.

37:19.220 --> 37:22.388
Turns out Nate is
part of a database of cases

37:22.390 --> 37:23.481
that were under review

37:23.483 --> 37:25.909
after all of these
social-justice uprisings

37:25.911 --> 37:29.061
and is eligible
for immediate release

37:29.063 --> 37:30.580
due to
gross negligence.

37:30.582 --> 37:32.690
He is on his way
to the island now.

37:32.692 --> 37:34.066
You know,
this is my life.

37:34.068 --> 37:35.643
This is
my daughter's life.

37:35.645 --> 37:38.237
You don't get to just
make decisions that affect us.

37:38.239 --> 37:40.982
You know, I have offered you
everything I could think of

37:40.984 --> 37:42.834
to earn your trust,
including an apology.

37:42.836 --> 37:45.762
I should be able to do this
for you as a father.

37:45.764 --> 37:47.322
♪♪

37:47.324 --> 37:51.676
One apology doesn't erase
years of abandonment.

37:51.678 --> 37:53.419
Neither does
a family bracelet

37:53.421 --> 37:55.438
or a letter
or your connections.

37:55.440 --> 37:57.107
You were never
a father to me.

37:57.109 --> 38:00.018
Stop trying
to be one now.

38:00.020 --> 38:02.279
♪♪

38:06.192 --> 38:09.027
He was so smug,
so proud of himself.

38:09.029 --> 38:10.862
Like, son,
you don't know my life.

38:10.864 --> 38:12.238
He doesn't know
what this means

38:12.240 --> 38:13.531
for me,
for Nikki.

38:13.533 --> 38:14.940
And what about Nate,
who's just gonna be

38:14.942 --> 38:16.275
dropped into
this new world.

38:16.277 --> 38:17.852
I mean,
the audacity.

38:17.854 --> 38:19.129
You want
a piece of this cake?

38:19.131 --> 38:20.613
'Cause it's good.

38:20.615 --> 38:22.114
Why are you
so calm?

38:22.116 --> 38:23.949
You trust Teddy Franklin
less than I do.

38:23.951 --> 38:25.302
You don't got
nothing to say?

38:25.304 --> 38:27.721
You don't want to hear
what I got to say.

38:34.204 --> 38:35.628
I want to hear
what you got to say.

38:35.630 --> 38:37.705
No, you want to see
some furniture moving

38:37.707 --> 38:40.025
up in
this Mickey flick.

38:41.969 --> 38:43.969
Alright, fine.
You want the real-real?

38:43.971 --> 38:46.047
This ain't about Teddy.

38:46.049 --> 38:47.382
You just mad because
you're gonna have to

38:47.384 --> 38:49.826
step in some mess
that<i> you</i> made.

38:49.828 --> 38:51.069
You been lying
to baby girl

38:51.071 --> 38:53.270
about her father
for 17 years,

38:53.272 --> 38:54.998
and it stops tonight.

38:55.000 --> 38:57.241
You gonna
tell her the truth.

38:57.243 --> 38:58.743
Now!

38:58.745 --> 39:00.395
Threw away
my damn cake.

39:00.397 --> 39:03.656
It's a good dadgum
thing I thought to
get me a second slice.

39:03.658 --> 39:08.252
♪♪

39:08.254 --> 39:09.587
Oh!

39:09.589 --> 39:11.089
There you are.
Ha!

39:11.091 --> 39:13.850
I noticed you were not in
attendance tonight with Angela.

39:13.852 --> 39:16.019
How did
my father die?

39:16.021 --> 39:18.930
The story you've told me
all these years isn't true.

39:18.932 --> 39:21.841
Perhaps I misremembered.

39:21.843 --> 39:25.052
It was
a painful loss.

39:26.031 --> 39:28.031
I spent my whole life
believing your lie.

39:28.033 --> 39:29.591
Are you accusing me
of something?

39:29.593 --> 39:31.350
Why the story,
when he was found in his car?

39:31.352 --> 39:33.853
Because that's where
he shot himself in the head.

39:33.855 --> 39:35.187
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:35.189 --> 39:39.117
Your father
committed suicide.

39:39.119 --> 39:41.119
Your mother and I
made up that story

39:41.121 --> 39:43.121
for the
insurance company.

39:43.123 --> 39:44.714
We told them that
Calvin had been working

39:44.716 --> 39:46.198
at the time
of his death

39:46.200 --> 39:50.294
so that you and your mother
would be provided for!

39:50.296 --> 39:52.797
That would not
have happened

39:52.799 --> 39:55.875
if his death
had been reported as...

39:55.877 --> 39:57.227
self-inflicted.

39:57.229 --> 39:59.470
I hate to tell it to you
this way, son --

39:59.472 --> 40:00.805
I'm not your son.

40:00.807 --> 40:02.306
Teddy? Hey.

40:02.308 --> 40:05.460
Hey.
Hey, can I get some help?

40:05.462 --> 40:06.736
Somebody?!

40:06.738 --> 40:08.738
Teddy.
I heard yelling.

40:08.740 --> 40:10.407
I was supposed to meet
Mr. Franklin.

40:10.409 --> 40:13.151
How can I help you,
brother?
Help me
get him to the hospital.

40:13.153 --> 40:15.578
Call 911.
Tell them we're on the way.

40:15.580 --> 40:17.305
Hey.

40:17.307 --> 40:18.564
Teddy.

40:18.566 --> 40:20.308
Teddy.

40:20.310 --> 40:22.067
I talked to him last week.
I want that exclusive.

40:22.069 --> 40:23.753
So you need
to follow --
As much as I want

40:23.755 --> 40:26.330
Teddy to pay for what he's done,
my marriage comes first.

40:26.332 --> 40:28.758
You have to leave.
Let's go for a little ride.

40:28.760 --> 40:30.485
[ Scoffs ]
Driver.

40:30.487 --> 40:32.670
I never would have answered
your call if I'd known

40:32.672 --> 40:34.764
I'd be chased out of town
by a Dupont again.

40:34.766 --> 40:36.266
What do you mean
"again"?

40:38.103 --> 40:41.512
20 years ago, I wasn't
your mother's vision

40:41.514 --> 40:43.773
of the perfect woman
for her perfect son.

40:43.775 --> 40:45.166
Leah was.

40:45.168 --> 40:47.110
Olivia and Teddy made sure
that their little prince

40:47.112 --> 40:48.853
and princess
could get married

40:48.855 --> 40:52.190
and create the dynasty
that they both dreamed of.

40:52.192 --> 40:55.176
Your mother wrote me a check
to get out of town.

40:55.178 --> 40:57.845
You took money to walk away
from our marriage?

40:57.847 --> 40:59.622
♪♪

40:59.624 --> 41:00.957
[ Sighs ]

41:00.959 --> 41:02.850
Olivia and Teddy threatened

41:02.852 --> 41:05.520
to have my parents deported,
Raymond.

41:05.522 --> 41:07.371
I had no choice.

41:07.373 --> 41:17.140
♪♪

41:17.142 --> 41:19.642
It's a lot of money.

41:19.644 --> 41:21.460
I never cashed it.

41:21.462 --> 41:24.797
I keep it as a reminder
that everything I have,

41:24.799 --> 41:26.708
I earned myself.

41:26.710 --> 41:28.710
I didn't know.

41:28.712 --> 41:32.655
♪♪

41:32.657 --> 41:35.325
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

41:35.327 --> 41:36.718
Leah.

41:36.720 --> 41:38.052
Okay, okay, okay.

41:38.054 --> 41:41.572
Calm down.
Calm down, babe.

41:41.574 --> 41:43.725
I'm on my way.

41:43.727 --> 41:44.892
Is everything okay?

41:44.894 --> 41:47.486
Teddy had
a heart attack.

41:47.488 --> 41:49.230
Take me
to Oak Bluffs Hospital.

41:49.232 --> 41:50.565
Man:
Yes, sir.

41:50.567 --> 41:52.825
[ Laughs ]

41:52.827 --> 41:54.435
I'm too hyped
to go to sleep.

41:54.437 --> 41:56.495
I've never had
an experience like this,

41:56.497 --> 42:00.908
and I-I don't want tonight
to end.

